I Yearn For Your Sweet TD's - 12 Team Keeper League



League/Keeper rules (RULE IN PLACE):

   - Unlimited number of keepers for each team
   - $100 minimum buy-in which locks in one keeper slot



Trade review (RULE IN PLACE)

   - All trades will undergo a 48 hour trade review where other teams have
   a chance to counter and offer better trade agreements.
   - If a trade is countered successfully, at least one of the players in
   the trade has to be a part of the new countered trade
   - 48 hour timer starts from the acceptance of the original trade, any
   successful counters DO NOT reset the timer on the trade



Draft capital cost (RULE IN PLACE)

   - The league will track the draft rounds that players are selected in in
   order to determine the draft capital cost of a keeper
   - Example: If a player is selected in the 6th round of the 2023 Draft,
   his cost in subsequent years is as follows
      - 2024: 5th round draft pick
      - 2025: 4th round draft pick
      - 2026: 3rd round draft pick
      - 2027: 2nd round draft pick
      - 2028 and beyond: 1st round draft pick
   - Note: Players acquired via trade have a slightly different treatment
   to their draft capital cost. As they are only partially owned for the
   season their draft capital cost does not rise in the initial subsequent
   year, however, continues the draft capital cost schedule as indicated
   above. Below is a comparison between the two different treatments based on
   a straight up player for player trade
   -

   Scenario A/Manager X

   Player drafted 2023 6th Round

   Kept through 2028

   Scenario B/Manager Y

   Player drafted 2023 6th Round

   Traded away in 2023

   Kept through 2028

   2024: 5th round draft pick

   2025: 4th round draft pick

   2026: 3rd round draft pick

   2027: 2nd round draft pick

   2028: 1st round draft pick

   2024: 6th round draft pick

   2025: 5th round draft pick

   2026: 4th round draft pick

   2027: 3rd round draft pick

   2028: 2nd round draft pick



Monetary cost (RULE IN PLACE)

   - ORIGINAL RULE: Aside from the initial $100 fee (includes one keeper)
   to renew your annual membership in the league, the cost of each additional
   keeper is $100 per player with no limit to the number of keepers


   - RULE IN PLACE: A more progressive approach has been taken to assign a
   higher monetary cost for 1st round players of $200 and reducing in monetary
   cost for each subsequent rounds. Initial $100 league membership renewal
   fee still only guarantees one keeper slot  and cannot be used to purchase
   additional slots
      - Round 1: $200
      - Round 2: $100
      - Round 3: $80
      - Round 4: $60
      - Round 5: $40
      - Round 6-9: $25
      - Round 10-16: $10



Waiver Wire Adds (RULE IN PLACE)

   - A monetary and draft capital cost needs to be associated with players
   that are added off of waivers.
   - As a player picked up off of waivers was never associated with a draft
   pick, the latest round draft capital cost and lowest monetary cost will
   be applied i.e. Round 16 pick and $10 price, etc.
   - If multiple waiver add players are being selected as keeper, their
   draft and cost will be assessed based on the week that they were claimed
      - An early week waiver add will have a higher cost
      - A later week waiver add will have a loser cost
      - If two players, one drafted and one claimed off of waivers, meet
      the same cost criteria, the player acquired off of waivers will
be assigned
      to the closest available draft slot and associated $ cost.
Drafted players
      have priority over their slots
   - If a manager drafts a player, drops him throughout the season, and
   picks that player back up off of waivers, the player is treated as a waiver
   wire add and not as a drafted player



Trades and their cost (Proposal)

   - Players acquired via trade will off-set the draft capital cost for one
   more additional subsequent year and then resume the Draft Capital Cost
   schedule
      -

      Scenario A/Manager X

      Player drafted 2023 6th Round

      Kept through 2028

      Scenario B/Manager Y

      Player drafted 2023 6th Round

      Traded away in 2023

      Kept through 2028

      2024: 5th round draft pick

      2025: 4th round draft pick

      2026: 3rd round draft pick

      2027: 2nd round draft pick

      2028: 1st round draft pick

      2024: 6th round draft pick

      2025: 5th round draft pick

      2026: 4th round draft pick

      2027: 3rd round draft pick

      2028: 2nd round draft pick



Monetary cost of a keeper via trade (PROPOSAL): Players acquired via trade
only cost half of the $ monetary value for the initial subsequent year

   -

   Scenario A/Manager X

   Player drafted 2023 6th Round

   Kept through 2028

   Scenario B/Manager Y

   Player drafted 2023 6th Round

   Traded away in 2023

   Kept through 2028

   2024: $40

   2025: $60

   2026: $80

   2027: $100

   2028: $200

   2024: $20

   2025: $60

   2026: $80

   2027: $100

   2028: $200



Players traded for a draft pick (PROPOSAL) are now assessed a cost basis one
round lower than that of the draft pick used in the trade in order to
account for the fact that the team acquiring the player no longer has a
pick of equal value available as it has been traded away. Example:

   - Manager X  trades away Patrick Mahomes to Manager Y and receives a 3rd
   round draft pick in return
   - Manager Y receives Patrick Mahomes but no longer has a 3rd draft to
   slot him into as a keeper for the subsequent year. What does Manager Y
   do?
      - If available, the manager uses  the new assigned draft capital cost
      of one round lower for that player i.e. Mahomes becomes a draft
      capital cost of round 4 and a monetary cost of round 4
      - If not available, the player has the right use a higher draft
      capital cost for the initial subsequent year i.e. round 2 in this
      scenario. The monetary cost remains round 4.
      - Regardless of the draft capital cost used to secure Mahomes as a
      keeper, his keeper value is reset and now follows the schedule
for the out
      years of a round 4 draft capital cost and monetary cost



Keeper selection process & available draft slots (REITERATION OF ABOVE
PROPOSALS)

   - A conflict currently exists where a team may want to keep two players
   that have the same keeper cost
      - Manager Y
         - Drafted a 6th round player they would like to keep
         - Acquired a player with a 6th round cost via trade and would like
         to keep him as well
      - How can Manager Y proceed to keep both players?
         - Trade either of the two players away in the off-season before
         the off-season trade deadline
         - Drop a player during the keeper selection process
         - If a higher draft round is available the TRADED player can be
         moved to it but retains their cost basis for future years
         - If no higher draft cost is available, or the manager is
         unwilling to use a higher pick, then the manager needs to
choose one player
         to occupy the draft slot and drop the other



Draft Order (PROPOSAL)

   - Playoff Teams: Will be determined by their regular season points and
   playoff results in reverse order.
      1. Pick 12: Champion
      2. Pick 11: Runner-up
      3. Pick 10: Loser in semifinal with highest season points
      4. Pick 9: Loser in semifinal with lowest season points
      5. Pick 8: Loser in quarterfinal with highest season points
      6. Pick 7:  Loser in quarterfinal with lowest season points
   - Non-playoff Teams: Will be based on a lottery system that provides the
   last place teams with an a better opportunity of getting the first round
   pick.
      -

      Odds of Pick 1:

      25%

      12th Place

      Odds of Pick 1:

      25%

      11th Place

      Odds of Pick 1:

      15%

      10th Place

      Odds of Pick 1:

      15%

      9th Place

      Odds of Pick 1:

      10%

      8th Place

      Odds of Pick 1:

      10%

      7th Place



Playoff Seeding (PROPOSAL)

   - 1-5 playoff seeding will be determined based on regular season win v
   loss standings
   - 6 playoff seed will be given to the team with highest regular season
   total points with the W-L record being the tiebreaker and W-L record
   between the two teams being the final tiebreaker. Beyond that it will have
   to be a coin-flip. Highly doubt we ever get to the first tie breaker



Fantasy Team Co-Manager (PROPOSAL)

   - As this league moves towards requiring more monetary capital to
   participate and compete, any team is allowed to seek out a co-manager
   outside of the league to assist them in the day-to-day operations of their
   team as they see fit
   - A co-manager is required to split the cost of entry into the league as
   well as the cost of keepers 50/50 with the other manager
   - Co-manager candidates need to be introduced to the team via a written
   persuasive letter or presentation highlighting their merits and reason for
   adding them as a co-manager
   - Co-managers are required to pay a one-time $100 initiation fee to join
   - Each team is allowed a total of two managers, maximum

